{
  "stem": "3360.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But when I was nine-- when I was 9 o'clock-- when I was nine years old, my mother enrolled me in the temple, the reform temple, in Hamburg, for instruction.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I-- from the first-- I wasn't very enthusiastic at first.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But from the very first visit there, I was so impressed with the kindness and with the way they went about telling us, and instructing us, and teaching us what all the various things where that are in a temple-- the bima and everything else.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we celebrated the holidays.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I have only, only really very good memories about then.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, my mother-- we did not keep the Sabbath and we did not keep kosher.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I, you know, can't talk very much about that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I know that when my grandmother, my mother's mother, was living-- when she died in 1916, way before I was born-- that they did have a kosher home.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then my grandfather, her father-- my mother's father-- was left with six children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And while they weren't little anymore, they did not keep kosher anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So that, that was not a very big part in my life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "German only.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I don't recall, I don't recall celebrating Hanukkah, the new year, and Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In my earlier years, until I started to go to the Jewish school, I had several, several classmates in my grade school who were Jewish, and there were also several there who were half-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there weren't any who were that religious or that observing in their home, because then they would have been enrolled originally, at first grade, at the Jewish, what we call here, day school.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's a Jewish school that teaches Hebrew from the first grade and has all Jewish teachers.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
